05/02/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH court sentenced brothers Ranko and Rajko Vukovic on Monday (February 4th) to 12 years in prison each for war crimes committed in the eastern Bosnian town of Foca in May 1992.
The court said the two brothers killed two Muslim civilians in the village of Podlokum, near Foca, while serving in the Bosnian Serb army.
The court dropped rape charges against Ranko.
The brothers were arrested in July.
(AFP, RTRS, PBS - 04/02/08)
